issue.title: `ws` throws `TypeError: Cannot use 'in' operator to search for 'code' in undefined` when with Deno
issue.body:
### Which package is this bug report for?

ws

### Issue description

1. Use deno, Make a simple Discord bot.
2. Leave the bot running for a long time. (Maybe 1 day?)
3. The bot suddenly throws an error and dies.

Error : `TypeError: Cannot use 'in' operator to search for 'code' in undefined`
Location: https://github.com/discordjs/discord.js/blob/main/packages/ws/src/ws/WebSocketShard.ts#L794

If I manually modify the conditional statement locally as follows, the problem no longer occurs.
But I'm not sure if it's okay to do this.

```js
onError(error) {
  if (error && "code" in error && ["ECONNRESET", "ECONNREFUSED"].includes(error.code)) {
```

I'm not sure if this is due to differences between Deno and Node.js, but I suspect it is.

### Code sample

_No response_

### Versions

- discord.js 14.15.3
- Deno 1.44.0

### Issue priority

Low (slightly annoying)

### Which partials do you have configured?

No Partials

### Which gateway intents are you subscribing to?

Guilds, GuildMessages, MessageContent

### I have tested this issue on a development release

_No response_

comment.body: Yes, this has been done for v15/dev. It cannot be done for v14 in a non-breaking way.

comment.body:
> There's nothing we can do about it. According to the Deno issue, `@discordjs/ws`@`1.x` should work now as of Deno 2.x
> 
> As per 2.0 usage in `discord.js`, use the dev version, it's not coming to v14.

What do you mean by, "There's nothing we can do about it"?

Isn't the obvious answer here to update to ws 2.0?

feat(voice)!: add new encryption methods, remove old methods (#10451)

BREAKING CHANGE: This library no longer supports using `tweetnacl` as an encryption library due to Discord deprecating the algorithms that `tweetnacl` helped us support (read more [here](https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log#voice-encryption-modes)). Please migrate to one of: `sodium-native`, `sodium`, `@stablelib/xchacha20poly1305`, `@noble/ciphers` or `libsodium-wrappers` unless your system supports `aes-256-gcm` (verify by running `require('node:crypto').getCiphers().includes('aes-256-gcm')`).
